# @podlite/publisher

=head1 Upcoming

=head1 0.0.20

=item extend Selector parsing: C<file:> scheme with suffix-match against C<publishRecord.file>, and pipe-separated block-name filters (e.g. C<file:terms.podlite | defn, para>). C<include-resolve-plugin> now inlines every matched block at the C<=include> location, not just the first
=item add glob support in C<file:> selectors: C<**> (any depth), C<*> (within segment), C<?> (single char). Enables patterns like C<=include file:00-DayByDay/**/term-*.podlite | defn> for full auto-aggregation across a directory tree
=item move C<parseSelector> and C<runSelector> implementation to C<@podlite/schema>. These names are still re-exported from this package, so downstream consumers that import them from C<@podlite/publisher> keep working without changes. The move breaks a circular-dependency risk for renderer-side packages that need selector mechanics (e.g. live-preview C<=include> resolution)

=head1 0.0.11

=item implement Selector for `doc:<NAME|ID>`

=head1 0.0.6

=item implement resolvers for `=include` block

=head1 0.0.5

=item initial support for `=Include` blocks and Selectors (https://podlite.org/specification#Selectors)
=item add support for embeded data using `=data` block
=item refactor existed and added new plugins:
  - docs-injector-plugin
  - dump-pages-plugin
  - include-resolve-plugin.spec
  - prev-next-plugin

=head1 0.0.4

=item add template configuration attribute for site: `:templateFile<file path>`
=item fix publishRecord

=head1 0.0.3

=item fix deps

=head1 0.0.1

=item plugins :breadcrumb-plugin, links-plugin, terms-index-plugin
=item support tempating for docs
=item fix processing templates
=item add helper `isExistsDocBlocks`
